                              Angular -front end tecnology
                                ------------------------
              basic commands
               =============
1.creation an Angularproject   -  ng new project-name
2.to run Angular project    -  ng serve
3.component creation     -  ng g component-name
4.service creation     -   ng g s service-name

                  basic concept
                  ============
1.module-to import 3rd party library-root module-appmodule


2.component-html,css,ts


3.to set up path for component---app routing module file


4.routing outlet selector


5.angular service


6.dependancy injection - inside the constructor

   syntax: access specifier object-name:dependent-class-name


7.asynchronus -rxjs - observable - subscribe()  


8.Data Binding - sharing data inside the component 
                                                                                        ts-component
                                                                                              html-view
8.1 one way binding(sharing data from one direction)

    8.1.1 component to view
           8.1.1.1 string interpolation - {{variable - name}}
           8.1.1.2 property binding -[attribute]="property-name"
    
    8.1.2 view to component
            8.1.2.1  event Binding - (event)="function-call"
             8.1.2.1  event Binding Using $ervent - (event)="function-call($event)"  (keyup)
             8.1.2.3 template reference variables, #variable name

8.2 two way binding
          8.2.1 ngModel   (template driven form)  - import formsmodel , [(ngModel)]="variable-name"    
                                                   - ngSubmit - apply it in form tag ,(ngSubmit)="function call"  




9. Angular directive - to manipulate DOM
     9.1 component directive 
     9.2 structural directive - add or remove any html element
         9.2.1 *ngIf="condition"  (it is a structural directive) //(*addstrict)
         9.2.2 *ngFor="let variable-nmae of array-name"
                                        (syntax for(let i of array-name))
10.ActivatedRoute
        Provides access to information about a route associated with a component                                 
11. router class - use navigateByUrl() to navigate one page to another using ts  
12. pipe - to convert user input to another format                                    